article.headline: Cornell 55, Lehigh 45
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Lenny Collins scored 14 points and Khaliq Gant scored all of his nine points on second-half 3-pointers to help Cornell rally to a 55-45 win over Lehigh on Tuesday night. Lehigh (6-7) opened the game with an 11-0 run, but Cornell (5-7) held the Mountain Hawks scoreless in the last seven minutes of the first half and trailed 19-15 at halftime. After going 0-for-9 from beyond the arc in the first half, the Big Red got hot from long range after halftime, hitting all six of their 3-point attempts and leading by as much as 13 after the break. Joe Knight led Lehigh with 14 points. Neither team shot well in the first half, Cornell going just 6-for-23 while Lehigh made 7 of 20 shots. Lehigh's point total was the lowest since the Mountain Hawks' 48-point performance against Colgate in February.
